result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating w/PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating w/PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Chareunsack Phrachomphonh was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

(Clerked by RWinger) 8:00 AM Defendant Chareunsack Phrachomphonh in court with attorney Aaron Olson. Angela Lynn Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Jurors not present. Defendant wishes to hire private counsel. Court questions Defendant. Court finds no grounds to discharge counsel. Proceed with Jury Trial today. 8:07 Court in recess.
(Clerked by ABarnes) 8:38 Case recalled. Defendant does not waive right to private voir dire.
(S. Millermon, Clerk) 8:40 20 jurors seated. 8:48 Court in session. All jurors sworn. Court voir dire. 9:15 No State voir dire. Voir dire by Attorney Olson. 9:18 Peremptory strikes made. 9:28 12 jurors sworn. Jurors excused. 9:30 Motions discussed. 1- 4 of State's motion - no objection by defense and Court grants. State's motion 5 - defense objects. Arguments by counsel. Court grants State's motion. Defense motions: 1 - granted. 2 - granted. 3 - All other witnesses are excluded. Court grants. 4 - no issue. Defense stipulates to three priors. No mention of priors. Redacted Informing the Accused form - no objection. Defense motion regarding citizen witnesses - objection to playing 911 calls. Arguments by counsel. Court finds an exception to hearsay rule and allows. Defense moves to preclude two witnesses from speculating as to why vehicle was swerving. Court grants. 9:40 Court recesses for 15 minutes.
(Clerked by ABarnes) 9:56 Case recalled outside presence of jury. 9:59 Jury seated - Court gives opening instructions 10:00 Opening Statement by State 10:12 Opening Statement by Attorney Olson 10:16 Jeff O. called and sworn - Direct by State - Exhibit 1 911 Call offered by State and received, Exhibit 2 Written Statement offered by State and received 10:31 Cross exam by Attorney Olson 10:34 Redirect by State 10:36 Scarlet C. called and sworn - Direct by State - Exhibit 3 911 Call offered by State and received 10:44 Cross exam by Attorney Olson 10:45 Deputy Jacob Winkler called and sworn - Direct by State, Exhibit 4 Informing the Accused offered by State and received, Exhibit 5 Blood/Urine Analysis Form offered by State - Objection by Attorney Olson - Ruling withheld (Court did not receive), Exhibit 6 Squad Cam Video offered by State - Objection by Attorney Olson (Court did not receive) 11:14 Jurors exit; Court questions defendant as to prior offenses and defendant stipulates to prior offenses - Court finds defendant's stipulation is knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily given and allows the stipulation 11:21 Jurors return and Exhibit 6 played for the jury 11:30 Attorney Olson objects and jury exits courtroom; Argument by Attorney Olson - Argument by State - Court relates - Rebuttal by Attorney Olson - Court relates - Discussion held 11:40 Court does not find intentional but is prejudicial and grants mistrial.  JT rescheduled for 3/9/16 #1. 11:55 Defense moves to amend bond to remove PBT condition - State objects - Court denies request.
